      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p><strong>What is a Myconid?</strong><br>A myconid is a humanoid fungal entity from speculative xenomycology. They walk, think, and occasionally teach undergraduate philosophy.</p>
      <p><strong>What is Mycology?</strong><br>The study of fungi ‚Äî their biology, reproduction, and troubling influence on political behavior.</p>
      <p><strong>UC Borehamwood? That place melting ice caps with flamethrowers?</strong><br>No official documentation supports this. The university‚Äôs Climatological Flamethrower Initiative concluded in 2012.</p>
